cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.GR 

This paper deals with 3D shape classification using deep neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a novel attention mechanism and reinforcement learning approach, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The application of the proposed method in multi-view active object recognition by a robot suggests a connection to robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the use of grayscale images and CNN architecture indicates a potential relevance to graphics (cs.GR).
